>
>
>
> I thought b) was a reasonable manual approach (e.g., Skiena, "The
> algorithm design manual, 2nd ed", p. 67), but I think I've read that for
> std::vector, a) (with push_back), is a better choice than b) (using
> reserve, not resize).
