> X
     [,1] [,2]
[1,] "Z"  "A" 
[2,] "z"  "A" 

However, instead of f returning a CharacterMatrix as it currently does, I'd like to return a CharacterVector Y, where each element of Y is a "collapsed" row of the updated X.

