Message-ID: <50D211F4.1070608@r-enthusiasts.com>

I suspect this is about your float[] not being initialized. I would 
recommend you to have a look at containers such as std::vector<> from 
the STL.


But this is a version that only uses Rcpp classes:


#include <Rcpp.h>
using namespace Rcpp ;

// [[Rcpp::export]]
NumericVector test_func(NumericMatrix my_matrix){
     int num_cols = my_matrix.ncol(); // extract matrix dimensions

     NumericVector my_expr(num_cols);  // output array

     for(int j = 0; j < num_cols; j++) {
         double sum_ = sum( my_matrix(_,j) ) ;
         my_expr[j] = sum_ / ( sum_ + j ) ;
     }
     return my_expr;
}

Put this in a file (foo.cpp) and then do:

 > sourceCpp( "foo.cpp" )
 > test_func( my_matrix)
[1] 1.0000000 0.6666667 0.0000000 0.4000000 0.5000000 0.2857143 0.3333333
[8] 0.3000000

This uses the Rcpp sugar sum function to sum a column: my_matrix(_,j) is 
a view on the j^th column.


Romain

